---
title: Chicken Sausage, Spinach & Chickpea Soup with Italian Herbs & Spices
description: No matter the weather, it’s tough not to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the culinary equivalent of a bear hug). Enter this hearty, soul-warming rendition. It’s chock full of goodness—that is to say spiced chicken sausage, tender chickpeas, wilted spinach, and a bevvy of Italian herbs in a rich, tomatoey broth. Soup’s on!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/609be202b36cfe344154e100-13ce52b3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-sausage-spinach-chickpea-soup-609be202b36cfe344154e100-8c6f68c5.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 2160 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-spinach-and-chickpea-soup-609be202b36cfe344154e100
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} and @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir 2 1/2 cups @water{2 1/2%cups}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%units}, chickpeas, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer, covered, for ~{7%minutes}.

Once soup has simmered for 7 minutes, uncover pot and stir in @baby spinach{5%ounce}. Simmer, uncovered, until spinach has wilted, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide soup between bowls and serve.